        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 24–34. Theloris costata (Thunberg). 24, dorsal habitus. 25, ventral habitus. 26, head in ventral view. 27, meso- and metapleuron; 28–30, pygophore in dorsal (28), posterior (29), and ventral (30) views. 31, left paramere. 32–34, phallus in dorsal (32), ventral (33), and lateral (34) views. Scale bars: 1, 1, 0.5, 1, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5, 0.25, 0.25, 0.25, 0.25 mm.Abbreviations: cj, conjunctiva; dr, dorsal rim; dsd, ductus seminis distalis; p, paramere; pcj, process of conjunctiva; ph,phalloteca; sr, superior ridge; v, vesica; vr, ventral rim." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4574970/files/figure.png" .

